        <updateDate>2016-04-05T19:30:09Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>ABLE to Work Act of 2016</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code, with respect to ABLE accounts (tax-exempt savings accounts for persons with a disability), to allow: (1) an ABLE account beneficiary to make contributions to an ABLE account equal to the lesser of such beneficiary's compensation or an amount equal to the federal poverty line for a one-person household, and (2) a retirement savings tax credit for contributions to an ABLE account. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
